Description: Handle of pottery transport amphora. Rectangular stamp
Curator's comments: Only known from Petrie's drawing in his Journal, 1884-5, p.32, 7. Likely to be a theta not chi at the geninning, as with some known fourth-century stamps from Thasos, but the omission of the circle is odd in view of the two well-preserved examples in the British Museum, 2011,5003.259 and 271.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1472)
